# results/

All outputs (tables and figures) produced by running the scripts in
`scripts/`. Organized in two subdirectories, each with its own detailed
README:

```
results/
├── tables/    CSV / TEX outputs — metrics, statistical tests, ablations
│   └── README.md
└── figures/   PNG / PDF outputs — plots and diagrams
    └── README.md
```

- See `results/tables/README.md` for the full list of tables, grouped by
  data source (multiexchange / yahoo / yobit), with the script that
  generates each one.
- See `results/figures/README.md` for the full list of figures, same
  grouping.

## Reproducing results

Each file in `results/` is regenerated by running the corresponding
script in `scripts/` (see `scripts/README.md` for the pipeline order per
data source). Nothing here needs to be created manually — this directory
exists so the reported numbers and plots can be inspected without
re-running the full pipeline.

## Key outputs for the article

The central finding of the article — that naive evaluation protocols
substantially overestimate pump-and-dump detection performance — is
supported by:

- `results/tables/multiexchange_protocol_summary_v2.csv` and
  `results/tables/Yahoo_split_x_protocol_summary_v2.csv` (Biased vs
  Standard vs UltraStrict comparison, both data sources)
- `results/figures/Fig_Yahoo_Protocol_Collapse.pdf` (main collapse figure)
- `results/tables/Bootstrap_CI_v2.csv` and
  `results/tables/Yahoo_Standard_Bootstrap_CI_20features_v2.csv`
  (statistical significance of the collapse)

The detection-profitability disconnect (Level 4, YoBit empirical
validation) is supported by:

- `results/tables/level4_alert_coverage_summary.csv`
- `results/tables/level4_waves_chronology_v2.csv`
- `results/figures/yobit_premium_vs_forward_return.png`

## Note

Files are excluded from version control via `.gitignore` only if they
exceed GitHub's size limits; standard CSV/PNG outputs from these scripts
are small enough to be committed directly.
